TITLE: Implementing a Stage Change Tool in Ultravox API
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a custom tool that triggers stage changes in an Ultravox call. The tool responds with a 'new-stage' response type and provides updated parameters for the new stage.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fixie-ai/ultradox/blob/main/guides/callstages.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// HTTP handler for stage changes
app.post('/next-stage', (req, res) => {
  // Set the response type to create a new stage
  res.set('X-Ultravox-Response-Type', 'new-stage');

  // Return the configuration for the next stage
  res.json({
    systemPrompt: "You are now helping the user with XYZ. Be concise and focused.",
    voice: "nova",  // Change the voice for this stage
    // You can override any other stage-compatible properties here
  });
});

// Client-side tool for stage changes
const stageChangeTool = {
  name: "change_stage",
  description: "Changes to the next stage of the conversation",
  run: async () => {
    return {
      responseType: "new-stage",
      responseBody: {
        systemPrompt: "You are now in the final stage. Wrap up the conversation politely.",
        // Other parameters to change in the new stage
      }
    };
  }
};

```

