TITLE: Creating a Tool with HTTP Authentication in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a tool that uses HTTP Authentication with the Bearer scheme. It shows the tool definition with security requirements and how to pass the bearer token when creating a call.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fixie-ai/ultradox/blob/main/essentials/tools.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Create a tool that uses HTTP Authentication scheme 'Bearer'. When the tool is invoked it will receive an 'Authorization' header with value "Bearer your_token_here".
{
  "name": "stock_price"
  "definition": {
    "description": "Get the current stock price for a given symbol",
    "requirements": {
      "httpSecurityOptions": {
        "options": [
          "requirements": {
            "myServiceApiKey": {
              "httpAuth": {
                "scheme": "Bearer"
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}

// Pass the Bearer token during call creation
{
  "model": "fixie-ai/ultravox-70B"
  "systemPrompt": ...
  "selectedTools": [
    {
      "toolName": "stock_price"
      "authTokens": {
        "myServiceApiKey": "your_token_here"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

